  "text": "In this paper we review our construction of the product system of a CP semigroup. This is applied effectively to the analysis of the CP semigroups which we call quantized convolution semigroups: they are semigroups of B(L 2 (R)) obtained from a modified WeylMoyal quantization of convolution semigroups of Borel probability measures on R 2 . In general quantized convolution semigroups have unbounded generators. A prime example which falls in this class is the heat flow on the CCR algebra, considered earlier by Arveson [CITATION_1] and which remained unidentified. We show its minimal dilation is cocycle conjugate to a CAR/CCR flow of index 2, and more generally we prove that, contrary to previous speculation, all quantized convolution semigroups have type I minimal dilations.",
